A 'Sympetrum vicinum' is a species of dragonfly.
It is typically characterized by its bright red coloration.
However, females often have darker, more subdued coloration.
Its wings are transparent and it has a slender, elongated body.
This species can be found across North America, particularly in wetland habitats.
They are known to be migratory and can often be seen in large groups.
Overall, the 'Sympetrum vicinum' is an impressive and fascinating insect to observe.
